/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/sushimiso_dualmodel_1round_p4/rounds/round_1/round_summary_stderr.log:553:[{"id":"F-001","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Missing Access Control on initAuction allows complete token theft","locations":["0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:138-180"],"claim":"The initAuction function has no access control and can be called by anyone. An attacker can initialize an already-funded auction with themselves as admin, then call finalize() to steal all auction tokens.","impact":"If tokens have been deposited into the contract for an auction, any attacker can initialize the auction with themselves as admin and steal all tokens by calling finalize(). The attacker only needs to know the token address and that tokens are present in the contract.","paths":["1. Attacker observes auction token has been transferred to DutchAuction contract (via ERC20 balanceOf)","2. Attacker calls initAuction() with their address as _admin","3. Attacker calls finalize() to transfer all auction tokens to their controlled wallet"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Arbitrary wallet change after auction commitments","locations":["0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:606-613"],"claim":"setAuctionWallet function has no check to ensure auction has not started (commitmentsTotal == 0), allowing admin to change the payment destination wallet after participants have already committed funds.","impact":"Admin can change the wallet address to their own address after participants have committed ETH/tokens, stealing all auction proceeds.","paths":["1. Participants commit funds to auction","2. Admin calls setAuctionWallet(attackerControlledAddress)","3. Admin calls finalize() to send all funds to attacker-controlled address"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Inconsistent use of nonReentrant modifier","locations":["0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:263-285","0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:521-537","0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:545-560","0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:606-613"],"claim":"commitEth, setDocument, setDocuments, removeDocument, setList, and setAuctionWallet lack nonReentrant modifier while commitTokensFrom, withdrawTokens, cancelAuction, and finalize have it.","impact":"Functions without reentrancy protection are vulnerable to reentrant calls that could manipulate state variables or cause unexpected behavior.","paths":["1. Attacker calls commitEth in a reentrant manner","2. Attacker calls setAuctionWallet within the same transaction"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"High","confidence":"medium","title":"Division by zero in price calculation functions","locations":["0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:204-207","0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:364-370","0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:355-357"],"claim":"tokenPrice(), calculateCommitment(), and totalTokensCommitted() can revert due to division by zero if clearingPrice() returns 0 (when minimumPrice is 0).","impact":"Auction becomes unusable if clearing price is calculated as 0, causing all calls to these view functions to revert and breaking integration with off-chain tools.","paths":["1. Admin initializes auction with minimumPrice = 0 (or minimum price calculated results in 0)","2. Any user calling tokenPrice(), calculateCommitment(), or totalTokensCommitted() gets division by zero error"]},{"id":"F-005","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Deprecated Solidity version 0.6.12","locations":["0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:1"],"claim":"Contract uses Solidity 0.6.12 which is an older version with known issues and has reached end-of-life.","impact":"Using deprecated compiler versions may introduce security vulnerabilities that have been fixed in newer versions. Code may be incompatible with modern tooling.","paths":[]},{"id":"F-006","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Outdated .transfer() pattern for ETH transfers","locations":["0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Utils/SafeTransfer.sol:28"],"claim":"_tokenPayment uses .transfer() which only provides 2300 gas (EIP-1884), while _safeTokenPayment uses .call() which is the recommended pattern.","impact":"ETH transfers via _tokenPayment may fail for contracts that require more than 2300 gas, causing the transaction to revert.","paths":[]},{"id":"F-007","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Comment and code discrepancy for finalizeTimeExpired","locations":["0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:404-408"],"claim":"The comment states '14 days' but the code uses '7 days' (block.timestamp + 7 days).","impact":"Confusing for integrators who rely on documentation. May lead to incorrect assumptions about auction finalization timing.","paths":[]},{"id":"F-008","severity":"Low","confidence":"high","title":"Wallet address can trigger finalization","locations":["0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:463-469"],"claim":"The wallet address (payment recipient) is allowed to call finalize(), creating a conflict of interest.","impact":"Wallet owner can finalize the auction themselves, potentially before the intended timeout, to gain early access to funds.","paths":[]},{"id":"F-009","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"IERC20 interface requires permit which many tokens lack","locations":["0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/interfaces/IERC20.sol:15-23","0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Utils/BoringBatchable.sol:52-63"]